title: Aegean
altText: Agean cat sitting on red couch.
text: Agean cats are some of the oldest cat breeds. Common feral cats in Greece and Turkey. They are meadium sized.

title: American Curl
altText: American Curl cat stading on a hardwood floor.
text: American Curls are well known for their ears, which curl backwards. The kittens are born with straight ears that later develop the signature curl. These cats are medium sized.

title: Aphrodite Giant
altText: Aphrodite Giant cat laying down on a bed.
text: Aphrodite Giant cats have thick hair. they are generally and energetic breed. they mostly live in mountain aresas, but are able to adapt to most climates.

title: Asian
altText: Orange Asian cat sitting upright on a blue blanket.
text: Asian breeds of cats are similar to the Burmese breed, just with more colors and patterns.
coatPattern: All without white and without siamese pointing

title: Birman
altText: CLose up of a Birman cats face as it stands in some tall green grass.
text: Birman cats were almost wiped out after world war two. Birman cats have blue eyes, and longer fur.

title: Chantilly-Tiffany
altText: Black Chantilly-Tiffany breed cat standing in front of a light brown background.
text: The breed is considered Extinct. they are often a chocolate color.
coatPattern: Solid, classic tabby, spotted tabby and ticked tabby

title: European Shorthair
altText: European Shorthair sitting on a table.
text: These cats are very healthy overall, and are natural hunters.

title: Egyptian Mau
altText: Egyptian Mau breed standing infront of a dark blue background.
text: These are a very rare breed. They are extremly fast. Its back legs are longer than its front legs.

title: Highlander
altText: Highlander cat standing on the corner of some stairs.
text: Highlanders originated as a cross breed. They have short tails, and curled ears.

title: Himalayan
altText: Close up of a Himalayan cat with blue eyes.
text: Similar to persian cats, with long hair and blue eyes. their ears are smaller than normal.

title: Kinkalow
altText: Black and white spotted Kinkalow cat being held while looking at the camera.
text: Kinkalows are an experimental breed, a crossbreed between Munchkin and the American Curl.

title: Maine Coon
altText: Brown and black Maine Coon cat facing towards the camera.
text: One of the oldest natural breeds. They are very large and friendly. They are a very popular and well-known breed.

title: Minuet
altText: White Minuet cat sitting on the ground.
text: These cats often have many health issues.

title: Munchkin
altText: Small white cat looking upwards with a blue background.
text: Well known for their short legs. There is alot of controversy about their health and mobility. Munchkin cats are also very small.

title: Norwegian Forest
altText: Fluffy ornage cat standing facing the left.
text: Norwegian Forest cats are intelligent and friendly. They are great with people and have alot of energy. As well as that their meows are often very high pitched.
coatPattern: Chocolate or orange and white bicolor

title: Pixie-bob
altText: Two Pixie-bob cats standing side by side in the grass.
text: These cats have black fur on their paws and tips of their ears. These cats are intellegent and highly active.

title: Ragdoll
altText: Ragdoll cat standing facing right on a light yellow background.
text: Ragdolls are known for being very calm and floppy cats. They are one of the largest domesticated cat breeds.

title: Savannah
altText: Spotted Savannah cat sitting on a white blanket.
text: Savannah cats are tall and slim, with distinct color markings.

title: Scottish Fold
altText: Grey Scottish Fold laying on the ground looking at the camera.
text: Scottish Folds are well known for their bent ears. Due to health concerns, breeding them is illegal in some places.

title: Toybob
altText: Toybob cat being held and looking off to the left.
text: Known for their small size and kinked tails. This is an Experimental cat breed.
